  <h1>Grid</h1>
  <p>The grid is based on 12 equal width columns.</p>
  <p>Construct grid using a combination of <code>.row</code> and <code>.col-mq-n</code>, where <strong>mq</strong> indicates the mq breakpoint. mq can be <strong>xs(mobile)</strong>, <strong>sm(mobile landscape)</strong>, <strong>md(tablet)</strong>, <strong>lg(desktop)</strong>, <strong>xl(wide)</strong>. <strong>n</strong> is the number of columns the element should span.
  <p>For full width columns, no <code>.col-mq-n</code> class is required</p>
  <p><code>.row</code> should always be within a <code>.container</code> since a negative margin is applied to the row to offset the padding applied to the columns it contains.</p>

  <div class="styleguide-example">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 bg--c">.col-md-4</div>
        <div class="col-md-4 bg--d">.col-md-4</div>
        <div class="col-md-4 bg--e">.col-md-4</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-3 bg--d">.col-md-3</div>
        <div class="col-md-6 bg--f">.col-md-6</div>
        <div class="col-md-3 bg--c">.col-md-3</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 bg--c">.col-md-3</div>
        <div class="col-md-4 bg--d">.col-md-6</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

